newsitem.title: AUSTRALIA: RTRS-Goodman Fielder shares top turnover.
newsitem.headline: RTRS-Goodman Fielder shares top turnover.

text.p: Shares in Australasian bakery and milling group Goodman Fielder Ltd topped turnover on Tuesday with 8.26 million shares or about 0.67 percent of the issued capital traded.
The bulk of the trade was in two lines, one of three million and one of five million, specialled by County Natwest.
Both parcels were traded at A$1.29 per share.
A spokesman for the company was unavailable for comment but the company has said previously that such a level of trade was relatively small in percentage terms.
Goodman has 1.23 billion shares on issue.
In response to repeatedly high turnover levels, chief executive David Hearn said on August 7 that the company had not received any takeover approaches.
By 2.25 p.m. (0425 GMT), Goodman shares were steady at A$1.29 on turnover of 9.66 million shares.
